laboratory_examinations.findings: Blood flow successfully drawn back into the true lumen without endoleak and aortic branches malperfusion, except for the obvious reflux from the distal tear.
Good positioning of the stent graft, bare stents, and coils, with normal blood flow to the aorta, patent visceral artery, and vanished false lumen.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Eighteen months postprocedure, the false lumen completely disappeared without clinical or surgical complications.
